Preheat broiler, with rack 6 inches (15 cm) from heat source Broil ribs, turning once, until lightly browned on both sides, about 7 minutes per side. Drain on paper towels and transfer to slow cooker stoneware. In a skillet, heat oil over medium heat for 30 seconds. Add onions and cook, stirring, until softened, about 3 minutes. Add garlic, cinnamon stick, oregano, salt, peppercorns and allspice; cook, stirring, for 1 minute. Add apples, tomatoes with juice and ½ cup (125 ml) of the stock; bring to a boil. Pour sauce over ribs. Cover and cook on Low for 5 hours or on High for 2½ hours, until ribs are tender and falling off the bone. About an hour before recipe has finished cooking, combine ancho chiles and boiling water in a heatproof bowl. Set aside for 30 minutes, weighing chiles down with a cup to ensure they remain submerged. Drain, discarding soaking liquid and stems, and coarsely chop chiles. Transfer to a blender and add bananas, jalapeno, vinegar and the remaining stock; purée. 5. Add chile mixture to stoneware, along with pineapple, and stir well. Cover and cook on High for 30 minutes, until hot and bubbly and flavors meld. Discard cinnamon stick and allspice. MAKE AHEAD MAKE AHEAD